lh.library/background                                 lh.library/background

   PURPOSE

   lh.library provides LHA archive compression, decompression, and archive
   container access for Amiga.  It replaces the classic 1990 lh.library
   with a full LHA engine (lh0-lh7, lzs, lz4, lz5) while retaining the
   original four buffer functions at the same LVO offsets for binary
   compatibility and legacy preservation.

   Version 2 adds a DOS.library-style archive API: LhArchive objects act as
   volume roots, LhLock/LhExamine/LhExNext traverse entries like directories,
   and LhOpenFromLock/LhRead/LhClose read decompressed file data.

   BOOTSTRAP

   LhBase = OpenLibrary("lh.library", 2L);

   No separate init or shutdown LVO is required.  Internal allocations use
   a pooled Exec memory arena freed when the library expunges.

   LINKING TIERS

   Tier 0 -- lh.library + <proto/lh.h>  (preferred)
     Shared library; use <libraries/lh.h> for public types and constants.

   Tier 1 -- lh.lib static core
     Codec and buffer API only, linked into one executable.

   TYPICAL TIER 0 FLOW (buffer encode/decode)

   LhBase = OpenLibrary("lh.library", 2L);
   buf = CreateBuffer(FALSE);
   buf->lh_Src = plain; buf->lh_SrcSize = plain_len;
   buf->lh_Dst = comp;  buf->lh_DstSize = sizeof(comp);
   n = LhEncode(buf);
   buf->lh_Src = comp; buf->lh_SrcSize = n;
   buf->lh_Dst = back; buf->lh_DstSize = plain_len;
   LhDecode(buf);
   DeleteBuffer(buf);
   CloseLibrary(LhBase);

   TYPICAL TIER 0 FLOW (archive read)

   arc = LhOpenArchive("RAM:Archive.lha", LHARC_MODE_READ);
   lock = LhLock(arc, "");
   LhExamine(lock, fib);
   while (LhExNext(lock, fib)) { /* list entries */ }
   LhUnLock(lock);
   LhCloseArchive(arc);

   OWNERSHIP AND LIFETIME

   - CreateBuffer returns an LhBuffer; always free it with DeleteBuffer.
   - Do not allocate struct LhBuffer yourself.
   - LhOpenArchive returns an opaque LhArchive; close with LhCloseArchive.
   - Locks from LhLock are not dos.library locks; free them with LhUnLock.
   - LhOpenFromLock does not take ownership of the lock; the caller still
     LhUnLock()s after LhClose().  LhOpen creates an internal lock that
     LhClose frees.
   - LhReadData returns an AllocMem buffer; the caller FreeMem()s it.

   ERROR MODEL

   Archive LVOs set a library-local error code retrieved with LhErr().
   Codes are dos.library IoErr-style values (ERROR_OBJECT_NOT_FOUND,
   ERROR_NO_MORE_ENTRIES, etc.).  Buffer LVOs return 0 on failure.
   See lh.library/errors.

   INCLUDE FILES

   #include <libraries/lh.h>
   #include <proto/lh.h>

   SEE ALSO
       lh.library/errors, lh.library/constants, SDK/Examples/LhTest.c
lh.library/errors                                     lh.library/errors

   GENERAL INFORMATION

   Classic buffer LVOs (CreateBuffer, LhEncode, LhDecode, LhCompress,
   LhDecompress) return NULL or 0 on failure and do not update LhErr().

   Archive LVOs store a dos.library-style error code in the library base.
   Call LhErr() after a failed call, similar to dos.library/IoErr.

   COMMON CODES

   ERROR_OBJECT_NOT_FOUND (205)
       Archive path or entry name not found.

   ERROR_OBJECT_EXISTS (203)
       May appear as a stale IoErr after path-removal retries.

   ERROR_NO_FREE_STORE (103)
       Memory allocation failed.

   ERROR_NO_MORE_ENTRIES (232)
       LhExAll finished the catalog (normal completion).

   ERROR_READ_PROTECTED (224)
       Archive open/catalog parse failed (not necessarily DOS protection).

   ERROR_WRITE_PROTECTED (223)
       Archive write, add, delete, or rewrite failed.

   ERROR_OBJECT_WRONG_TYPE (212)
       Lock or handle used with the wrong operation.

   ERROR_INVALID_COMPONENT_NAME (210)
       NULL or empty path/name argument.

   ERROR_LINE_TOO_LONG (120)
       LhExAll buffer too small for the next record.

   ERROR_BAD_NUMBER (115)
       LhExAll Type not in ED_NAME..ED_COMMENT.

   SEE ALSO
       LhErr(), dos.library/IoErr, lh.library/background
lh.library/constants                                  lh.library/constants

   GENERAL INFORMATION

   Constants and types are defined in <libraries/lh.h>.

   LIBRARY

   LH_NAME           "lh.library"
   LH_VERSION        2
   LH_MIN_VERSION    2
   ENCODEEXTRA(n)    (((n) + 7) >> 3)  -- extra bytes for LhEncode dest

   ARCHIVE MODES (LhOpenArchive)

   LHARC_MODE_READ    MODE_OLDFILE  -- open existing archive for read
   LHARC_MODE_WRITE   MODE_NEWFILE  -- create/truncate archive for write
   LHARC_MODE_APPEND  1007L         -- append entries to existing archive

   LHADD_* TAGS (LhAddEntryTagList / LhAddEntryTags)

   LHADD_Method     (TAG_USER+1) -- compression level (0=store, 5=lh5, ...)
   LHADD_Attrs      (TAG_USER+2) -- Amiga protection bits
   LHADD_DateStamp  (TAG_USER+3) -- struct DateStamp *
   LHADD_Comment    (TAG_USER+4) -- STRPTR filenote (ext 0x41)

   BUFFER (struct LhBuffer)

   lh_Src / lh_SrcSize   -- input buffer and length
   lh_Dst / lh_DstSize   -- output buffer and capacity (updated on success)
   lh_Aux / lh_AuxSize   -- internal work area (set by CreateBuffer)
   lh_Reserved           -- reserved; leave zero

   CODEC METHODS (LhCompress / LhDecompress)

   Method numbers match the LHA method table (0 = lh0/store, 5 = lh5, ...).
   See <lh.h> LH_METHOD_* when linking the static core.

   SEE ALSO
       lh.library/background, CreateBuffer(), LhOpenArchive()
lh.library/CreateBuffer                               lh.library/CreateBuffer

   NAME
       CreateBuffer -- Allocate an LhBuffer with work area  (V2)

   SYNOPSIS
       buffer = CreateBuffer(OnlyDecode);
       D0                    D0

       struct LhBuffer *CreateBuffer(LONG OnlyDecode);

   FUNCTION
       Allocates a struct LhBuffer and its internal auxiliary work area.
       Do not allocate LhBuffer yourself; always obtain it from this LVO
       and free it with DeleteBuffer().

       OnlyDecode selects the work-area size: TRUE allocates a smaller
       decode-only buffer (about 4500 bytes), FALSE allocates a larger
       encode+decode buffer (about 40000 bytes).

   INPUTS
       OnlyDecode - TRUE for decode-only aux buffer, FALSE for encode+decode.

   RESULT
       buffer - pointer to LhBuffer, or NULL on failure.

   EXAMPLE

       struct LhBuffer *buf;

       buf = CreateBuffer(FALSE);
       if (!buf) {
           /* allocation failed */
       }

   NOTES

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO
       DeleteBuffer(), LhEncode(), LhDecode(), LhCompress(), LhDecompress()
lh.library/DeleteBuffer                               lh.library/DeleteBuffer

   NAME
       DeleteBuffer -- Free an LhBuffer from CreateBuffer  (V2)

   SYNOPSIS
       DeleteBuffer(OldBuffer);
                    A0

       VOID DeleteBuffer(struct LhBuffer *OldBuffer);

   FUNCTION
       Frees the LhBuffer and its auxiliary work area allocated by
       CreateBuffer().  Pass NULL safely (no-op).

   INPUTS
       OldBuffer - buffer from CreateBuffer(), or NULL.

   RESULT
       None.

   EXAMPLE

       DeleteBuffer(buf);
       buf = NULL;

   NOTES

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO
       CreateBuffer()
lh.library/LhEncode                                   lh.library/LhEncode

   NAME
       LhEncode -- Compress a buffer (classic LhEncode / lh5)  (V2)

   SYNOPSIS
       size = LhEncode(Buffer);
       D0              A0

       ULONG LhEncode(struct LhBuffer *Buffer);

   FUNCTION
       Compresses Buffer->lh_Src (lh_SrcSize bytes) into Buffer->lh_Dst.
       The destination must be at least lh_SrcSize + ENCODEEXTRA(lh_SrcSize)
       bytes.  lh_Src and lh_Dst must not overlap.

       Lhassa uses standard LHA lh5 compression (not the 1990 proprietary
       Lh format).  On success, lh_DstSize is updated to the compressed size.

   INPUTS
       Buffer - LhBuffer with lh_Src/lh_SrcSize and lh_Dst/lh_DstSize set.

   RESULT
       size - compressed size in D0 and lh_DstSize, or 0 on error.

   EXAMPLE

       static UBYTE plain[] = "sample payload";
       static UBYTE comp[128];
       ULONG n;

       buf->lh_Src = plain;
       buf->lh_SrcSize = (ULONG)(sizeof(plain) - 1);
       buf->lh_Dst = comp;
       buf->lh_DstSize = (ULONG)sizeof(comp);
       n = LhEncode(buf);

   NOTES

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO
       LhDecode(), CreateBuffer(), LhCompress()
lh.library/LhDecode                                   lh.library/LhDecode

   NAME
       LhDecode -- Decompress a buffer (classic LhDecode / lh5)  (V2)

   SYNOPSIS
       size = LhDecode(Buffer);
       D0              A0

       ULONG LhDecode(struct LhBuffer *Buffer);

   FUNCTION
       Decompresses Buffer->lh_Src (lh_SrcSize bytes) into Buffer->lh_Dst.
       lh_DstSize must be large enough for the full uncompressed payload.
       lh_Src and lh_Dst must not overlap.

   INPUTS
       Buffer - LhBuffer with compressed source and output capacity set.

   RESULT
       size - decompressed size, or 0 on error.

   EXAMPLE

       buf->lh_Src = comp;
       buf->lh_SrcSize = n;
       buf->lh_Dst = plain;
       buf->lh_DstSize = original_len;
       n = LhDecode(buf);

   NOTES

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO
       LhEncode(), CreateBuffer(), LhDecompress()
lh.library/LhCompress                                 lh.library/LhCompress

   NAME
       LhCompress -- Compress a buffer with an explicit method  (V2)

   SYNOPSIS
       size = LhCompress(Method, Buffer);
       D0                D0      A0

       ULONG LhCompress(LONG Method, struct LhBuffer *Buffer);

   FUNCTION
       Compresses Buffer->lh_Src into Buffer->lh_Dst using Method (for
       example 0 for lh0/store, 5 for lh5).  Same buffer rules as LhEncode.

   INPUTS
       Method - LHA method number.
       Buffer - LhBuffer with source and destination set.

   RESULT
       size - compressed size, or 0 on error.

   EXAMPLE

       ULONG n;

       n = LhCompress(0L, buf);   /* 0 = lh0 / store */

   NOTES

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO
       LhDecompress(), LhEncode(), lh.library/constants
lh.library/LhDecompress                               lh.library/LhDecompress

   NAME
       LhDecompress -- Decompress a buffer with an explicit method  (V2)

   SYNOPSIS
       size = LhDecompress(Method, Buffer);
       D0                  D0      A0

       ULONG LhDecompress(LONG Method, struct LhBuffer *Buffer);

   FUNCTION
       Decompresses Buffer->lh_Src into Buffer->lh_Dst using Method.
       Same buffer rules as LhDecode.

   INPUTS
       Method - LHA method number used when the data was compressed.
       Buffer - LhBuffer with source and destination set.

   RESULT
       size - decompressed size, or 0 on error.

   EXAMPLE

       ULONG n;

       n = LhDecompress(0L, buf);

   NOTES

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO
       LhCompress(), LhDecode(), lh.library/constants
lh.library/LhOpenArchive                              lh.library/LhOpenArchive

   NAME
       LhOpenArchive -- Open an LHA archive as a volume root  (V2)

   SYNOPSIS
       archive = LhOpenArchive(Path, Mode);
       D0                      D1    D0

       struct LhArchive *LhOpenArchive(STRPTR Path, LONG Mode);

   FUNCTION
       Opens Path as an LHA archive.  Mode is LHARC_MODE_READ,
       LHARC_MODE_WRITE, or LHARC_MODE_APPEND.

       Read mode builds an in-memory catalog of entries.  Write mode
       creates or truncates the archive.  Append mode adds entries to an
       existing archive (or creates it if missing).

       On failure, LhErr() returns a dos-style error code.

   INPUTS
       Path - archive file path.
       Mode - LHARC_MODE_READ, LHARC_MODE_WRITE, or LHARC_MODE_APPEND.

   RESULT
       archive - opaque archive handle, or NULL on failure.

   EXAMPLE

       struct LhArchive *arc;

       arc = LhOpenArchive("RAM:Archive.lha", LHARC_MODE_READ);
       if (!arc) {
           Printf("open failed, LhErr %ld\n", LhErr());
       }

   NOTES

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO
       LhCloseArchive(), LhLock(), LhAddEntry(), LhErr()
lh.library/LhCloseArchive                             lh.library/LhCloseArchive

   NAME
       LhCloseArchive -- Close an archive from LhOpenArchive  (V2)

   SYNOPSIS
       success = LhCloseArchive(Archive);
       D0                       A0

       LONG LhCloseArchive(struct LhArchive *Archive);

   FUNCTION
       Closes the archive, flushes any writer state, and frees the
       LhArchive and its catalog.  Do not use the pointer afterward.

   INPUTS
       Archive - handle from LhOpenArchive(), or NULL (fails).

   RESULT
       success - DOSTRUE on success, DOSFALSE on failure.

   EXAMPLE

       if (!LhCloseArchive(arc)) {
           Printf("close failed, LhErr %ld\n", LhErr());
       }
       arc = NULL;

   NOTES

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO
       LhOpenArchive()
lh.library/LhLock                                     lh.library/LhLock

   NAME
       LhLock -- Lock an archive entry or the archive root  (V2)

   SYNOPSIS
       lock = LhLock(Archive, Name);
       D0            A0       A1

       BPTR LhLock(struct LhArchive *Archive, STRPTR Name);

   FUNCTION
       Returns a lock on Name within Archive, or on the archive root when
       Name is NULL or "".  The lock is not a dos.library lock; free it
       only with LhUnLock().

       Root locks are used with LhExamine/LhExNext/LhExAll.  Entry locks
       are used with LhOpenFromLock and LhNameFromLock.

   INPUTS
       Archive - open archive (typically LHARC_MODE_READ).
       Name    - entry path, or NULL/"" for the archive root.

   RESULT
       lock - lock handle, or NULL if not found (see LhErr()).

   EXAMPLE

       BPTR lock;

       lock = LhLock(arc, "");              /* archive root */
       lock = LhLock(arc, "readme.txt");    /* one entry */

   NOTES

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO
       LhUnLock(), LhExamine(), LhExNext(), LhOpenFromLock(),
       dos.library/Lock
lh.library/LhUnLock                                   lh.library/LhUnLock

   NAME
       LhUnLock -- Free a lock from LhLock  (V2)

   SYNOPSIS
       success = LhUnLock(Lock);
       D0                 A0

       LONG LhUnLock(BPTR Lock);

   FUNCTION
       Frees a lock obtained from LhLock().  After LhOpenFromLock(), the
       caller still owns the lock and must LhUnLock() it after LhClose().

   INPUTS
       Lock - lock from LhLock(), or NULL (fails).

   RESULT
       success - DOSTRUE on success, DOSFALSE on failure.

   EXAMPLE

       LhUnLock(lock);

   NOTES

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO
       LhLock(), LhClose(), dos.library/UnLock
lh.library/LhExamine                                  lh.library/LhExamine

   NAME
       LhExamine -- Fill a FileInfoBlock for a lock  (V2)

   SYNOPSIS
       success = LhExamine(Lock, Fib);
       D0                  A0    A1

       LONG LhExamine(BPTR Lock, struct FileInfoBlock *Fib);

   FUNCTION
       Fills Fib for Lock.  On an archive root lock, returns the first
       catalog entry and prepares LhExNext() for subsequent entries
       (same pattern as dos.library/Examine + ExNext).

       On an entry lock, fills Fib for that entry only.

   INPUTS
       Lock - lock from LhLock().
       Fib  - FileInfoBlock to fill.

   RESULT
       success - DOSTRUE on success, DOSFALSE on failure.

   EXAMPLE

       struct FileInfoBlock *fib;

       fib = (struct FileInfoBlock *)AllocMem(
           (ULONG)sizeof(struct FileInfoBlock), MEMF_PUBLIC | MEMF_CLEAR);
       if (LhExamine(lock, fib)) {
           Printf("%s\n", fib->fib_FileName);
       }

   NOTES

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO
       LhExNext(), LhLock(), dos.library/Examine
lh.library/LhExNext                                   lh.library/LhExNext

   NAME
       LhExNext -- Advance to the next archive entry  (V2)

   SYNOPSIS
       success = LhExNext(Lock, Fib);
       D0                 A0    A1

       LONG LhExNext(BPTR Lock, struct FileInfoBlock *Fib);

   FUNCTION
       Continues a directory walk started by LhExamine() on a root lock.
       Fills Fib with the next catalog entry.  Returns DOSFALSE when no
       more entries remain.

   INPUTS
       Lock - root lock previously used with LhExamine().
       Fib  - FileInfoBlock to fill.

   RESULT
       success - DOSTRUE if another entry was returned, DOSFALSE at end.

   EXAMPLE

       while (LhExNext(lock, fib)) {
           Printf("%8ld  %s\n", fib->fib_Size, fib->fib_FileName);
       }

   NOTES

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO
       LhExamine(), LhExAll(), dos.library/ExNext
lh.library/LhExAll                                    lh.library/LhExAll

   NAME
       LhExAll -- Examine multiple archive entries into a buffer  (V2)

   SYNOPSIS
       success = LhExAll(Lock, Buffer, Size, Type, Control);
       D0                A0    D1      D0    D2    A1

       LONG LhExAll(BPTR Lock, STRPTR Buffer, LONG Size, LONG Type,
           struct ExAllControl *Control);

   FUNCTION
       Fills Buffer with linked ExAllData records for entries under a
       root lock (ED_NAME through ED_COMMENT).  Control must be from
       AllocDosObject(DOS_EXALLCONTROL, NULL) with eac_LastKey zeroed
       before the first call.

       Returns DOSTRUE while more catalog entries remain.  Returns
       DOSFALSE when complete (LhErr() == ERROR_NO_MORE_ENTRIES) or on
       error.  eac_Entries holds the number of records written by the
       call, including the final completing call.

       The archive index is built in memory, so LhExAll is typically
       faster than LhExamine/LhExNext.

   INPUTS
       Lock    - root lock from LhLock(arc, "").
       Buffer  - output buffer for ExAllData records.
       Size    - size of Buffer in bytes.
       Type    - ED_NAME .. ED_COMMENT.
       Control - ExAllControl (eac_LastKey, eac_Entries, optional match).

   RESULT
       success - DOSTRUE if more entries remain, DOSFALSE when done/error.

   EXAMPLE

       struct ExAllControl ctl;
       UBYTE buf[2048];

       memset(&ctl, 0, sizeof(ctl));
       ctl.eac_LastKey = 0;
       while (LhExAll(lock, (STRPTR)buf, (LONG)sizeof(buf),
           ED_NAME, &ctl)) {
           /* walk ExAllData records in buf */
       }

   NOTES

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO
       LhExAllEnd(), LhExNext(), dos.library/ExAll, LhErr()
lh.library/LhExAllEnd                                 lh.library/LhExAllEnd

   NAME
       LhExAllEnd -- Abort an in-progress LhExAll scan  (V2)

   SYNOPSIS
       success = LhExAllEnd(Lock);
       D0                   A0

       LONG LhExAllEnd(BPTR Lock);

   FUNCTION
       Aborts an in-progress LhExAll() scan on Lock (dos.library/ExAllEnd
       equivalent).  The next LhExAll() on that lock returns
       ERROR_NO_MORE_ENTRIES.

   INPUTS
       Lock - root lock used with LhExAll().

   RESULT
       success - DOSTRUE on success, DOSFALSE on failure.

   EXAMPLE

       LhExAllEnd(lock);   /* abort an in-progress LhExAll scan */

   NOTES

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO
       LhExAll(), dos.library/ExAllEnd
lh.library/LhInfo                                     lh.library/LhInfo

   NAME
       LhInfo -- Return volume-style info for an archive lock  (V2)

   SYNOPSIS
       success = LhInfo(Lock, Info);
       D0               A0    A1

       LONG LhInfo(BPTR Lock, struct InfoData *Info);

   FUNCTION
       Fills Info with summary data for the archive (block counts derived
       from catalog sizes).  Mirrors dos.library/Info for the archive
       volume.

   INPUTS
       Lock - any lock on the archive.
       Info - InfoData to fill.

   RESULT
       success - DOSTRUE on success, DOSFALSE on failure.

   EXAMPLE

       struct InfoData info;

       if (LhInfo(lock, &info)) {
           Printf("blocks used %ld\n", info.id_NumBlocksUsed);
       }

   NOTES

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO
       LhLock(), dos.library/Info
lh.library/LhOpenFromLock                             lh.library/LhOpenFromLock

   NAME
       LhOpenFromLock -- Open a file handle from an entry lock  (V2)

   SYNOPSIS
       fh = LhOpenFromLock(Lock, Mode);
       D0                   A0    D0

       BPTR LhOpenFromLock(BPTR Lock, LONG Mode);

   FUNCTION
       Opens a read handle for the entry referenced by Lock and loads the
       decompressed payload into memory.  Use LhRead/LhSeek/LhClose on
       the handle.

       Does not take ownership of Lock; the caller must still LhUnLock()
       after LhClose().

   INPUTS
       Lock - entry lock from LhLock() (not a root lock).
       Mode - open mode (typically MODE_OLDFILE).

   RESULT
       fh - file handle, or NULL on failure (see LhErr()).

   EXAMPLE

       BPTR fh;

       fh = LhOpenFromLock(elock, MODE_OLDFILE);
       /* caller still LhUnLock(elock) after LhClose(fh) */

   NOTES

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO
       LhOpen(), LhRead(), LhClose(), LhUnLock(), dos.library/OpenFromLock
lh.library/LhOpen                                     lh.library/LhOpen

   NAME
       LhOpen -- Open a named archive entry  (V2)

   SYNOPSIS
       fh = LhOpen(Archive, Name, Mode);
       D0           A0       A1    D0

       BPTR LhOpen(struct LhArchive *Archive, STRPTR Name, LONG Mode);

   FUNCTION
       Opens a named archive entry in one step (LhLock + LhOpenFromLock).
       Same role as dos.library/Open on a file within the archive volume.
       The internal lock is owned by the handle and freed by LhClose().

   INPUTS
       Archive - open archive.
       Name    - entry path within the archive.
       Mode    - open mode (typically MODE_OLDFILE).

   RESULT
       fh - file handle, or NULL on failure (see LhErr()).

   EXAMPLE

       BPTR fh;

       fh = LhOpen(arc, "readme.txt", MODE_OLDFILE);
       if (!fh) {
           Printf("open failed, LhErr %ld\n", LhErr());
       }

   NOTES

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO
       LhOpenFromLock(), LhRead(), LhClose(), dos.library/Open
lh.library/LhRead                                     lh.library/LhRead

   NAME
       LhRead -- Read from an archive entry handle  (V2)

   SYNOPSIS
       count = LhRead(Fh, Buffer, Len);
       D0             D1  A0      D0

       LONG LhRead(BPTR Fh, APTR Buffer, LONG Len);

   FUNCTION
       Reads up to Len bytes from Fh into Buffer.  Argument order matches
       dos.library/Read.

   INPUTS
       Fh     - handle from LhOpen() or LhOpenFromLock().
       Buffer - destination buffer.
       Len    - maximum bytes to read.

   RESULT
       count - bytes read, 0 at EOF, or -1 on error.

   EXAMPLE

       UBYTE buf[256];
       LONG n;

       n = LhRead(fh, buf, (LONG)sizeof(buf));
       if (n < 0) {
           /* read error */
       } else if (n == 0) {
           /* end of file */
       }

   NOTES

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO
       LhWrite(), LhSeek(), LhClose(), dos.library/Read
lh.library/LhWrite                                    lh.library/LhWrite

   NAME
       LhWrite -- Write to an archive entry handle  (V2)

   SYNOPSIS
       count = LhWrite(Fh, Buffer, Len);
       D0              D1  A0      D0

       LONG LhWrite(BPTR Fh, APTR Buffer, LONG Len);

   FUNCTION
       Writes Len bytes from Buffer to Fh.  Argument order matches
       dos.library/Write.

       Write support is reserved for archives opened for write/append.
       Handles opened for read reject writes (return -1).

   INPUTS
       Fh     - handle from LhOpen() or LhOpenFromLock().
       Buffer - source buffer.
       Len    - bytes to write.

   RESULT
       count - bytes written, or -1 on error / not writable.

   EXAMPLE

       LONG n;

       n = LhWrite(fh, data, (LONG)data_len);
       /* read-only handles return -1 */

   NOTES

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO
       LhRead(), LhAddEntry(), dos.library/Write
lh.library/LhClose                                    lh.library/LhClose

   NAME
       LhClose -- Close an archive entry handle  (V2)

   SYNOPSIS
       success = LhClose(Fh);
       D0                D1

       LONG LhClose(BPTR Fh);

   FUNCTION
       Closes Fh and frees its payload buffer.  If the handle was created
       by LhOpen(), the internal lock is also freed.  If the handle was
       created by LhOpenFromLock(), the caller still owns the lock and
       must LhUnLock() it.

   INPUTS
       Fh - handle from LhOpen() or LhOpenFromLock().

   RESULT
       success - DOSTRUE on success, DOSFALSE on failure.

   EXAMPLE

       LhClose(fh);

   NOTES

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO
       LhOpen(), LhOpenFromLock(), LhUnLock(), dos.library/Close
lh.library/LhSeek                                     lh.library/LhSeek

   NAME
       LhSeek -- Seek within an archive entry handle  (V2)

   SYNOPSIS
       pos = LhSeek(Fh, Position, Mode);
       D0           D1  D2        D0

       LONG LhSeek(BPTR Fh, LONG Position, LONG Mode);

   FUNCTION
       Sets the read/write position in Fh.  Mode is OFFSET_BEGINNING,
       OFFSET_CURRENT, or OFFSET_END (same as dos.library/Seek).

   INPUTS
       Fh       - handle from LhOpen() or LhOpenFromLock().
       Position - offset (interpretation depends on Mode).
       Mode     - OFFSET_BEGINNING, OFFSET_CURRENT, or OFFSET_END.

   RESULT
       pos - new position from start of entry, or -1 on error.

   EXAMPLE

       LONG pos;

       pos = LhSeek(fh, 0L, OFFSET_BEGINNING);
       pos = LhSeek(fh, 0L, OFFSET_END);

   NOTES

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO
       LhRead(), LhWrite(), dos.library/Seek
lh.library/LhNameFromLock                             lh.library/LhNameFromLock

   NAME
       LhNameFromLock -- Copy the entry name from a lock  (V2)

   SYNOPSIS
       len = LhNameFromLock(Lock, Buffer, Len);
       D0                   A0    A1      D0

       LONG LhNameFromLock(BPTR Lock, STRPTR Buffer, LONG Len);

   FUNCTION
       Copies the entry name for Lock into Buffer (NUL-terminated, at most
       Len-1 characters).  For a root lock, Buffer receives an empty string.

   INPUTS
       Lock   - lock from LhLock().
       Buffer - destination string buffer.
       Len    - size of Buffer in bytes.

   RESULT
       len - strlen of the name written, or 0 on failure.

   EXAMPLE

       TEXT name[256];

       if (LhNameFromLock(lock, name, (LONG)sizeof(name)) > 0) {
           Printf("%s\n", name);
       }

   NOTES

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO
       LhLock(), dos.library/NameFromLock
lh.library/LhAddEntry                                 lh.library/LhAddEntry

   NAME
       LhAddEntry -- Add a file entry to a writable archive  (V2)

   SYNOPSIS
       success = LhAddEntry(Archive, Name, Data, DataLen);
       D0                   A0       A1    A2    D0

       LONG LhAddEntry(struct LhArchive *Archive, STRPTR Name, APTR Data,
           LONG DataLen);

   FUNCTION
       Appends Name with payload Data (DataLen bytes) to Archive.  Archive
       must be opened with LHARC_MODE_WRITE or LHARC_MODE_APPEND.

       Defaults: header level 2 (path extension type 2 for nested names
       such as LIBS/foo.library), LH5 compression, Amiga attribute
       LH_ATTR_DEFAULT (0 = ----rwed), and the current DateStamp.  Basename
       "Manifest" is stored as LH0.  For method/attrs/date/comment
       overrides, use LhAddEntryTagList() or LhAddEntryTags().

   INPUTS
       Archive - archive opened for write or append.
       Name    - entry path within the archive (may contain '/').
       Data    - payload bytes (may be NULL only if DataLen is 0).
       DataLen - payload length in bytes.

   RESULT
       success - DOSTRUE on success, DOSFALSE on failure.

   EXAMPLE

       static STRPTR payload = (STRPTR)"hello";

       arc = LhOpenArchive("RAM:New.lha", LHARC_MODE_WRITE);
       LhAddEntry(arc, "greeting.txt", payload, 5L);
       LhCloseArchive(arc);

   NOTES

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO
       LhAddEntryTagList(), LhAddEntryTags(), LhOpenArchive(),
       LhDeleteFile(), LhConcatArchive()
lh.library/LhAddEntryTagList                    lh.library/LhAddEntryTagList

   NAME
       LhAddEntryTagList -- Add a file entry with a TagItem list  (V2)

   SYNOPSIS
       success = LhAddEntryTagList(Archive, Name, Data, DataLen, TagList);
       D0                          A0       A1    A2    D0       A3

       LONG LhAddEntryTagList(struct LhArchive *Archive, STRPTR Name,
           APTR Data, LONG DataLen, struct TagItem *TagList);

   FUNCTION
       Same as LhAddEntry(), but TagList may override compression method,
       Amiga protection bits, DateStamp, and filenote comment.

       Nested names (e.g. LIBS/foo.library) are written as header level 2
       with filename extension type 1 and path extension type 2 (0xFF
       separators).  Comments are stored as extension type 0x41 and
       restored as filenotes on LhExtractEntry / LhExamine.

   INPUTS
       Archive - archive opened for write or append.
       Name    - entry path (may contain '/').
       Data    - payload bytes (NULL only if DataLen is 0).
       DataLen - payload length.
       TagList - optional TagItem list ending in TAG_DONE, or NULL.

       LHADD_Method    (TAG_USER+1)  compression level (0=store, 5=lh5, ...)
       LHADD_Attrs     (TAG_USER+2)  Amiga protection bits → LHA attribute
       LHADD_DateStamp (TAG_USER+3)  struct DateStamp *
       LHADD_Comment   (TAG_USER+4)  STRPTR filenote

   RESULT
       success - DOSTRUE on success, DOSFALSE on failure (see LhErr()).

   EXAMPLE

       struct TagItem tags[4];
       struct DateStamp ds;

       DateStamp(&ds);
       tags[0].ti_Tag = LHADD_Attrs;
       tags[0].ti_Data = 0;  /* ----rwed (Amiga rwed bits are inverted) */
       tags[1].ti_Tag = LHADD_DateStamp;
       tags[1].ti_Data = (ULONG)&ds;
       tags[2].ti_Tag = LHADD_Comment;
       tags[2].ti_Data = (ULONG)"built by lh-handler";
       tags[3].ti_Tag = TAG_DONE;
       LhAddEntryTagList(arc, "LIBS/foo.library", data, len, tags);

   NOTES
       Without TagList, behaviour matches LhAddEntry() (LH5, Manifest→LH0).
       LhAddEntryTags() is the ==varargs alias for this LVO.

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO
       LhAddEntry(), LhAddEntryTags(), LhExtractEntry(), lh.library/constants
lh.library/LhAddEntryTags                          lh.library/LhAddEntryTags

   NAME
       LhAddEntryTags -- Varargs form of LhAddEntryTagList  (V2)

   SYNOPSIS
       success = LhAddEntryTags(Archive, Name, Data, DataLen,
                                firstTag, ...);
       D0                       A0       A1    A2    D0

       LONG LhAddEntryTags(struct LhArchive *Archive, STRPTR Name,
           APTR Data, LONG DataLen, Tag firstTag, ...);

   FUNCTION
       Same LVO as LhAddEntryTagList() (SFD ==varargs).  Not a separate
       FuncTab entry; SAS/C exposes it via #pragma tagcall.

   EXAMPLE

       LhAddEntryTags(arc, "readme.txt", data, len,
           LHADD_Comment, (ULONG)"note",
           TAG_DONE);

   SEE ALSO
       LhAddEntryTagList(), LhAddEntry()
lh.library/LhDeleteFile                               lh.library/LhDeleteFile

   NAME
       LhDeleteFile -- Remove an entry from an archive  (V2)

   SYNOPSIS
       success = LhDeleteFile(Archive, Name);
       D0                     A0       A1

       LONG LhDeleteFile(struct LhArchive *Archive, STRPTR Name);

   FUNCTION
       Rewrites the archive excluding the named entry.  Same role as
       dos.library/DeleteFile on a file within the archive volume.

       The archive file is rewritten via a temporary file and rename.
       If Archive was opened for read, its catalog is rebuilt afterward.

   INPUTS
       Archive - open archive.
       Name    - entry path to remove.

   RESULT
       success - DOSTRUE on success, DOSFALSE on failure (see LhErr()).

   EXAMPLE

       if (!LhDeleteFile(arc, "obsolete.txt")) {
           Printf("delete failed, LhErr %ld\n", LhErr());
       }

   NOTES

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO
       LhAddEntry(), LhOpenArchive(), dos.library/DeleteFile
lh.library/LhConcatArchive                            lh.library/LhConcatArchive

   NAME
       LhConcatArchive -- Append all entries from another archive  (V2)

   SYNOPSIS
       success = LhConcatArchive(Dest, SourcePath);
       D0                        A0    A1

       LONG LhConcatArchive(struct LhArchive *Dest, STRPTR SourcePath);

   FUNCTION
       Appends all file entries from SourcePath into Dest (LhA "c" command).
       Dest must be opened with LHARC_MODE_WRITE or LHARC_MODE_APPEND.

   INPUTS
       Dest       - destination archive (write/append).
       SourcePath - path of source archive to read.

   RESULT
       success - DOSTRUE on success, DOSFALSE on failure (see LhErr()).

   EXAMPLE

       if (!LhConcatArchive(arc, "RAM:Donor.lha")) {
           Printf("concat failed, LhErr %ld\n", LhErr());
       }

   NOTES

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO
       LhAddEntry(), LhOpenArchive()
lh.library/LhSetPassword                              lh.library/LhSetPassword

   NAME
       LhSetPassword -- Set password for encrypted entries  (V2)

   SYNOPSIS
       success = LhSetPassword(Archive, Password);
       D0                      A0       A1

       LONG LhSetPassword(struct LhArchive *Archive, STRPTR Password);

   FUNCTION
       Associates Password with Archive for subsequent encrypted entry
       operations.  Pass "" to clear the password.

   INPUTS
       Archive  - open archive.
       Password - password string, or "" to clear.

   RESULT
       success - DOSTRUE on success, DOSFALSE on failure.

   EXAMPLE

       LhSetPassword(arc, "secret");
       /* ... read encrypted entries ... */
       LhSetPassword(arc, "");   /* clear */

   NOTES

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO
       LhOpenArchive(), LhReadData()
lh.library/LhReadData                                 lh.library/LhReadData

   NAME
       LhReadData -- Read a named entry into an AllocMem buffer  (V2)

   SYNOPSIS
       len = LhReadData(Archive, Name, DataOut);
       D0               A0       A1    A2

       LONG LhReadData(struct LhArchive *Archive, STRPTR Name, APTR *DataOut);

   FUNCTION
       Decompresses Name from Archive into a newly AllocMem'd buffer.
       *DataOut receives the buffer; the caller must FreeMem() it using
       the returned length.

       The byte count is returned only in D0 because SAS/C #pragma libcall
       does not reliably pass a fourth output pointer for size.

   INPUTS
       Archive - archive opened for read.
       Name    - entry path within the archive.
       DataOut - receives AllocMem pointer on success.

   RESULT
       len - decompressed byte count (>= 0), or -1 on error (see LhErr()).

   EXAMPLE

       APTR data;
       LONG len;

       data = NULL;
       len = LhReadData(arc, "readme.txt", &data);
       if (len >= 0 && data) {
           /* use data[0 .. len-1] */
           FreeMem(data, (ULONG)len);
       }

   NOTES

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO
       LhExtractEntry(), LhTestEntry(), LhOpen()
lh.library/LhExtractEntry                             lh.library/LhExtractEntry

   NAME
       LhExtractEntry -- Extract a named entry to a filesystem path  (V2)

   SYNOPSIS
       success = LhExtractEntry(Archive, Name, DestPath);
       D0                       A0       A1    A2

       LONG LhExtractEntry(struct LhArchive *Archive, STRPTR Name,
           STRPTR DestPath);

   FUNCTION
       Decompresses Name and writes it to DestPath.  Parent directories
       are created as needed.  After writing, applies catalog metadata:
       SetProtection (LHA attribute byte), SetFileDate, and SetComment
       (extension 0x41 filenote) when present.

   INPUTS
       Archive  - archive opened for read.
       Name     - entry path within the archive.
       DestPath - destination filesystem path.

   RESULT
       success - DOSTRUE on success, DOSFALSE on failure (see LhErr()).

   EXAMPLE

       if (!LhExtractEntry(arc, "readme.txt", "RAM:Out/readme.txt")) {
           Printf("extract failed, LhErr %ld\n", LhErr());
       }

   NOTES

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO
       LhReadData(), LhTestEntry()
lh.library/LhTestEntry                                lh.library/LhTestEntry

   NAME
       LhTestEntry -- Verify a named entry by decompressing it  (V2)

   SYNOPSIS
       len = LhTestEntry(Archive, Name);
       D0                A0       A1

       LONG LhTestEntry(struct LhArchive *Archive, STRPTR Name);

   FUNCTION
       Decompresses Name to verify integrity, then discards the buffer.
       Useful for archive testing without writing files.

   INPUTS
       Archive - archive opened for read.
       Name    - entry path within the archive.

   RESULT
       len - decompressed byte count on success, or -1 on error.

   EXAMPLE

       LONG len;

       len = LhTestEntry(arc, "readme.txt");
       if (len < 0) {
           Printf("test failed, LhErr %ld\n", LhErr());
       }

   NOTES

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO
       LhReadData(), LhExtractEntry()
lh.library/LhPrintEntry                               lh.library/LhPrintEntry

   NAME
       LhPrintEntry -- Write a named entry to the process Output()  (V2)

   SYNOPSIS
       success = LhPrintEntry(Archive, Name);
       D0                     A0       A1

       LONG LhPrintEntry(struct LhArchive *Archive, STRPTR Name);

   FUNCTION
       Decompresses Name and writes the payload to the current process
       Output() stream (typically the console).

   INPUTS
       Archive - archive opened for read.
       Name    - entry path within the archive.

   RESULT
       success - DOSTRUE on success, DOSFALSE on failure (see LhErr()).

   EXAMPLE

       LhPrintEntry(arc, "readme.txt");   /* writes to Output() */

   NOTES

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO
       LhReadData(), LhExtractEntry()
lh.library/LhErr                                      lh.library/LhErr

   NAME
       LhErr -- Return the last archive error code  (V2)

   SYNOPSIS
       code = LhErr();
       D0

       LONG LhErr(VOID);

   FUNCTION
       Returns the last archive error code stored in the library base
       (dos.library IoErr-style numbers).  Call after a failed archive
       LVO.  Classic buffer LVOs do not update this value.

   INPUTS
       None.

   RESULT
       code - last error code, or 0 if none.

   EXAMPLE

       arc = LhOpenArchive("nope.lha", LHARC_MODE_READ);
       if (!arc) {
           Printf("LhErr %ld\n", LhErr());
       }

   NOTES

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO
       lh.library/errors, dos.library/IoErr